According to the formulas for kinetic and potential energy, the Lagrangian function is:
$$
\begin{gathered}
\widetilde{L} = \frac{1}{2} m_{1} \dot{y}_{1}^{2} + \frac{1}{2} m_{2} \dot{y}_{2}^{2} + \frac{1}{2} \frac{I}{r^{2}} \dot{y}_{2}^{2} + \frac{1}{2} L_{1} \dot{q}_{1}^{2} + \frac{1}{2} L_{2} \dot{q}_{2}^{2} + M \dot{q}_{1} \dot{q}_{2} - \frac{1}{2 C_{1}} q_{1}^{2} \\
-\frac{1}{2 C_{2}} q_{2}^{2} + E_{1} q_{1} + E_{2} q_{2} - \frac{1}{2} \frac{k_{1}}{r^{2}} y_{2}^{2} - \frac{1}{2} k_{2}\left(b-y_{1}-y_{2}\right)^{2} - m_{1} g y_{1} - m_{2} g y_{2} 
\end{gathered}
$$

$$
